Sentencas: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFC) with La0.3Sr0.7TiO3 (LST)-yttria-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) anodes were prepared by impregnation of LST into porous YSZ scaffolds and then modified by Atomic Layer Deposition (ALD) of Ni, Pt, Pd, Fe, Co. and CeO2.
Titulo: Investigating the Catalytic Requirements of Perovskite Fuel Electrodes Using Ultra-Low Metal Loadings

Sentencas: Weight loadings as low as 0.01% of Pt, Ni, and Pd were sufficient to decrease anode impedances by orders of magnitude for operation in humidified H-2 at 973 K.
Titulo: Investigating the Catalytic Requirements of Perovskite Fuel Electrodes Using Ultra-Low Metal Loadings

Sentencas: The effects of CeO2, Co, and Fe were less but still significant.
Titulo: Investigating the Catalytic Requirements of Perovskite Fuel Electrodes Using Ultra-Low Metal Loadings

Sentencas: Sintering at higher temperatures was important.
Titulo: Investigating the Catalytic Requirements of Perovskite Fuel Electrodes Using Ultra-Low Metal Loadings

Sentencas: Possible ways of stabilizing the metal particles and implications for developing ceramic anodes are discussed.
